cs.LG, cs.CE, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.CY 

This paper involves the use of machine learning techniques to predict infant mortality rates using birth certificate data. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Other likely sub-categories include cs.CE (Computational Epidemiology) as the paper deals with predicting infant mortality rates, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as machine learning techniques are used, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as the paper discusses the societal impact of infant mortality rates, and cs.CY (Computers and Society) as the paper discusses the inequalities in infant mortality rates across different racial and ethnic groups.
